ðŸ“Œ What are Resources in Android?
Resources are external elements that you use in your app instead of hardcoding values directly in your code.
They help with:
Reusability (use the same color, string, or dimension in multiple places)
Maintainability (update a single resource instead of updating everywhere)
Localization & theming (support multiple languages, screen sizes, dark mode, etc.)

Common Resource Types:
res/values/strings.xml â†’ Text values (<string>, <string-array>)
res/values/colors.xml â†’ Color definitions
res/values/dimens.xml â†’ Dimensions (padding, margin, text sizes, etc.)
res/drawable/ â†’ Images, shapes, gradients, vectors
res/layout/ â†’ XML layout files (used less in Compose but still important)
res/mipmap/ â†’ App icons
res/raw/ â†’ Arbitrary raw files (e.g., JSON, audio, video)
res/font/ â†’ Custom fonts

ðŸ“Œ What are Qualifiers in Android?

Qualifiers are suffixes added to resource directories that tell Android which version of a resource to use depending on device configuration.

For example:
res/layout/activity_main.xml (default)
res/layout-land/activity_main.xml (for landscape orientation)
res/drawable-hdpi/logo.png (for HDPI screens)
res/values-en/strings.xml (for English language)
res/values-hi/strings.xml (for Hindi language)

ðŸ”¹ Common Resource Qualifiers
Screen density qualifiers
ldpi (low density, ~120 dpi)
mdpi (medium density, ~160 dpi)
hdpi (high density, ~240 dpi)
xhdpi, xxhdpi, xxxhdpi (higher resolutions)

Orientation qualifiers
res/layout/ (default portrait)
res/layout-land/ (landscape layout)
Screen size qualifiers
small, normal, large, xlarge
Example:
res/layout-large/

Locale (language & region)
res/values-en/strings.xml (English)
res/values-hi/strings.xml (Hindi)
res/values-fr-rCA/strings.xml (French, Canada)

Night mode
res/values/colors.xml (light mode)
res/values-night/colors.xml (dark mode)

API level
res/values-v21/ (resources for Android 5.0 and above)
res/values-v33/ (resources for Android 13 and above)

âœ… In short:
Resources = external assets (strings, layouts, drawables, etc.).
Qualifiers = conditions (screen size, orientation, locale, theme, API level) to pick the correct resource automatically.